      "note": "The chapter's rhetorical architecture is a two-panel triptych: Panel 1 (19:1-15) — systematic dismantling of every Egyptian institution, sealed by a prophetic formula (19:4) and a summary of total paralysis (19:15). Panel 2 (19:16-25) — five escalating 'In that day' oracles that reverse every element of Panel 1. The hinge is the repeated bayom hahu formula, which signals that what follows is not merely a historical prediction but an eschatological vision of Yahweh's ultimate purposes for the nations."
